# Proposal

## What will (likely) be the title of your project?
Is It Vegan?

## In just a sentence or two, summarize your project. (E.g., "A website that lets you buy and sell stocks.")
A webapp where you can upload a picture of a food product's barcode and it'll tell you whether it's vegan or not.

## In a paragraph or more, detail your project. What will your software do? What features will it have? How will it be executed?

A user will be able to either upload/scan a picture of a barcode or type in the barcode number into a form on the Is It Vegan web app. A program that I will write will then extract the code, look it up in a barcode database (I am using https://www.upcitemdb.com), determine the ingredients from the manufacturer (if documented and of course if the food item exists in the database), cycle through each listed ingredient and check if any of them are included in a comprehensive list of nonvegan ingredients (such as dairy, eggs, meat, honey, etc), and if there's a match it'll show the user that the food item is not vegan while if there is not match then it will display that it is vegan. I will also add the feature of "recent searches" so that a user can see their past recent lookups. It will be on a webapp using Flask.

