## In the world of software, most everything takes longer to implement than you expect. And so it's not uncommon to accomplish less in a fixed amount of time than you hope.

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a GOOD outcome for your final project. I.e., what WILL you accomplish no matter what?

My good outcome is ending up with a program that reads a barcode of a product and can display its ingredients (or else display a message saying that there's no information for that product available). 

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a BETTER outcome for your final project. I.e., what do you THINK you can accomplish before the final project's deadline?

On top of the good outcome, the better outcome would also include being able to somewhat accurately tell whether a food product is vegan or not and also I would accomplish creating a basic 
on which a user could interact with the program.

### In a sentence (or list of features), define a BEST outcome for your final project. I.e., what do you HOPE to accomplish before the final project's deadline?

I hope to accomplish the better outcome plus a very nice-looking webapp instead of just a basic website, as well as having the program be accurate at least 90% of the time. 

## In a paragraph or more, outline your next steps. What new skills will you need to acquire? What topics will you need to research? If working with one of two classmates, who will do what?

I will need to research how barcodes work, API's, pyzbar, openCV, and possibly webscraping. I'm also learning to use VSCode. I'll also need to somehow obtain or otherwise create a list of nonvegan ingredients. Ideally, I wanted to make a mobile app, but unfortunately that may be a project for another day because as of right now, I don't have the time to brave that learning curve. Instead, I'll make a website/web app, which means I'll have to learn more about using html, css, javascript, and flask. My next steps are researching and creating a csv file for nonvegan ingredients to look out for and also learning flask. I will also read documentation for pyzbar and openCV to try to get a better sense of how those work. I will use that research to write my program (which I have already started in python).
